        <div> <h6> Causes & Corrections</h6> </div>
        <div>
          <p> Shoulder-related computer strain is less common, but can occur when tension is held between the neck and wrist. 
              If either of these areas is strained, try correcting them first and see if the pain persists.</p>
          <p> If you experience shoulder pain in the mouse-arm, switching to a <b>vertical mouse</b> can often help. 
              By aligning the arm in a more neutral position, you can take much of the strain off of the internal rotator muscles.</p>
        </div>
