      <div class="bottom-L-window style-7 smr">
        <div>
          <h6> SMR Pressure-Point Massage</h6>
        </div>
        <div class="smr-card">
          <img class="trapezius" src="images/neck/Trapezius anatomy.jpeg">
          <img src="images/smr/SMR Thoracic spine.jpg">
          <p class="card-title"> Thoracic Spine SMR </p>
          <p class="directions"> Requires : Foam-roller or Tennis balls</p>
          <p class="directions"> Keeping the arms crossed, roll over the device to massage the muscles along your spine - from your neck to mid-back. </p>
          <p class="directions"> For safety, avoid rolling out the lower-back as this has little benefits and can aggravate pre-existing problems.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="smr-card">
          <img src="images/shoulders/pectoralis-minor-SMR.jpg">
          <p class="card-title"> Pectoralis Minor SMR </p>
          <p class="directions"> Requires : Tennis or Lacrosse ball</p>
          <p class="directions"> Apply circular rolling pressure by placing the ball between the pec and the shoulder. 
              Apply pressure using your bodyweight. This can be done laying face-down on the ground, or by leaning forward into a wall. </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bottom-R-window style-7 stretch">
        <div>
          <h6> Follow-up Stretches </h6>
        </div>
        <div class="stretch-card">
          <img src="images/neck/trapezius-side-stretch.jpg">
          <p class="card-title"> Trapezius Side Stretch </p>
          <p class="directions"> Tilt your head horizontally to the side, resting your hand on the top-side of your head. Push your head up into your hand, while using your arm to gently resist. </p>
          <p class="directions"> After holding this for as long as you can, release and allow yourself to sink deeper into the stretch. </p>
          <p class="directions"> Repeat for the other side. </p> 
        </div>
        <div class="stretch-card">
          <img src="images/shoulders/DOORWAY-PEC-STRETCH.jpg">
          <p class="card-title"> Chest Opening Stretch </p>
          <p class="directions"> Perform this stretch seated or standing. Interlock your fingers behind your back and look upward. Pull the shoulders back and downward. 
                                 Use a towel or partner for assistance if needed. </p>
          <p class="directions"> This can also be done while standing, using the frame of a doorway for support. </p>
        </div>
      </div>
